> Docker 29 is the latest version, but due to changes in how containers are built and possible memory usage increases, I'm keeping it at 28 for now.

@saiarcot895 FYI
Docker 29 uses [containerd image store](https://docs.docker.com/engine/storage/containerd/) by default. It stores layers both compressed and uncompressed, which increases disk usage and slows down builds — on my build machine with Docker 29, sonic-slave took a  couple extra minutes just for image packaging. Adding "features": {"containerd-snapshotter": false} to daemon.json switches back to overlay2. Maybe it's useful for the internal Docker too, but I haven't tested it. Either way, Docker 28 is a safer choice for now.

